headline: United Airlines’s (NASDAQ:UAL) Q3 Earnings Results: Revenue In Line With Expectations
summary: Airline company United Airlines Holdings (NASDAQ:UAL) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 2.6% year on year to $15.23 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.78 per share was 4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: United tops Q3 earnings with premium travel boost to thank
summary: United Airlines (UAL) beat third quarter earnings estimates — adjusted earnings figures of $2.78 per share (vs. estimates of $2.66), operating revenue of $15.23 billion just missing estimates of $15.28 billion — while illustrating growth in premium air travel bookings. Yahoo Finance senior reporter Pras Subramanian breaks down United's fourth quarter earnings guidance that outpaced Wall Street expectations. This comes after Delta Air Lines (DAL) topped third quarter earnings estimates last week. headline: United Airlines Continues to Win Brand-Loyal Customers as Q3 Profit and Q4 Outlook Both Exceed Wall Street Expectations
summary: United Airlines (UAL) today reported a third-quarter profit ahead of Wall Street expectations. The company had third-quarter pre-tax earnings of $1.3 billion, with a pre-tax margin of 8.2% and adjusted pre-tax earnings1 of $1.2 billion, with an adjusted pre-tax margin1 of 8.0%. The company also achieved diluted earnings per share of $2.90 and adjusted diluted earnings per share1 of $2.78, compared to guidance of $2.25 to $2.75. Total operating revenue grew 2.6% year-over year to $15.2 billion.
